{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_26","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > /tmp/design_pattern_notes.txt <<'EOF'\nRelevant precedent for GO:0061852\n- GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex is the generic cellular component parent for membrane cargo receptor complexes.\n- GO:0062136 low-density lipoprotein receptor complex shows the common pattern for a specific receptor complex: specific lexical label + definition describing the complex's receptor capability.\n- GO:0061852 currently uses transporter terminology, but the existing definition describes recognition/binding/return of ER resident proteins in vesicle-mediated retrograde traffic, which aligns better with cargo receptor semantics than transporter complex semantics.\n- No dedicated DOSDP file for cargo receptor complexes was found under src/design_patterns; ontology precedent should guide the edit.\n- Avoid adding new intersection_of axioms here because the issue only requests superclass/label/definition refinement and there is no documented pattern for a direction-specific retrograde cargo receptor complex.\nEOF\ncat /tmp/design_pattern_notes.txt\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
